This paper deals with fine-tuning transformer-based language models for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves experimentation and analysis of the effectiveness of different fine-tuning strategies, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses textual data for tasks such as semantic similarity and sentiment analysis, which could also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
